"{\"uid\": \"theconversation.com-paris-2024-olympics-how-the-games-are-being-used-to-marginalize-the-most-vulnerable-228855\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Assistant Professor Sport Management, Wilkes University  Assistant Professor, School of Kinesiology, Western University  Assistant Professor, Kinesiology, Western University  Lecturer in Psychology, Southampton Solent University  The authors do not work for, consult, own shares in or receive funding from any company or organisation that would benefit from this article, and have disclosed no relevant affiliations beyond their academic appointment.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 36, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_management\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sport Management\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_management\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_management\"}, {\"begin\": 38, \"end\": 55, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilkes_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wilkes University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilkes_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilkes_University\"}, {\"begin\": 101, \"end\": 119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Western_Ontario\", \"score\": 0.9999370034295997, \"rank\": 6.300053918024505e-05, \"text\": \"Western University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Western_Ontario\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Western_Ontario\"}, {\"begin\": 142, \"end\": 153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kinesiology\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.315910624652091e-23, \"text\": \"Kinesiology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kinesiology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kinesiology\"}, {\"begin\": 155, \"end\": 173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Western_Ontario\", \"score\": 0.9999370034295997, \"rank\": 6.300053918024505e-05, \"text\": \"Western University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Western_Ontario\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Western_Ontario\"}, {\"begin\": 199, \"end\": 228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solent_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Southampton Solent University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solent_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Solent_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Western Universityprovides funding as a member of The Conversation CA-FR.\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 454, \"end\": 461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9999425523677841, \"rank\": 5.745093257375723e-05, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}, {\"begin\": 504, \"end\": 520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2617904793960186e-27, \"text\": \"The Conversation\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Western Universityprovides funding as a member of The Conversation CA.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9999425523677841, \"rank\": 5.745093257375723e-05, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"View all partners  https://doi.org/10.64628/AAM.jg559gqms  Share article  Print article  Athletes from around the world are gearing up for the 2024 Summer Olympics that are being held in Paris this year.\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 788, \"end\": 793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999690948421616, \"rank\": 3.090611319287601e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Games are often billed as a beacon of global unity, they havehistorically marginalizedthe mostvulnerable communities in host cities.\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 947, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee (IOC) routinely makes grandiose claims about its commitment to humanity.\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 1057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 953, \"end\": 990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking over theOlympic Charterand the IOC's guiding philosophy of \\\"Olympism,\\\" it's hard not to be struck by the organization's promises, however empty they may be.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.018121785233279e-25, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It states:  \\\"The goal of Olympism is to place sport at the service of the harmonious development of humankind, with a view to promoting a peaceful society concerned with the preservation of human dignity.\\\"\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1429, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet,time and again, the Games have further disadvantaged some of the world's most marginalized people in host cities.\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For Paris 2024, the outcome will be no different.\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1598, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1553, \"end\": 1563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.301351386448287e-19, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The nations of the world will look the other way, ignore the consequences of the Games and celebrate a new crop of athletes - fulfilling the Olympic's motto of \\\"faster, higher, stronger\\\" - while embracing displacement, gentrification and bigotry.\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In April, hundreds of people, including displaced communities,were evictedfrom makeshift shelters in a camp south of Paris.\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1964, \"end\": 1969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999690948421616, \"rank\": 3.090611319287601e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is only the most recent example; police have carried outnumerous evictionsin therun-up to the Games.\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 2076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These evictions are a clear example of how the Olympic Games are used as a pretext to displace marginalized people to sanitize a host city's image beforethe global spectacle.\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Authorities say the evictions arenot connected to the Games.\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, in July 2023, a new law was passed imposing large fines and prison sentences for illegal occupation.\", \"from\": 2315, \"to\": 2424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Displaced communities encounter significantmental health risks, which primarily arise from theirprior experiences of false persecution,warand having to leave theirhome countries.\", \"from\": 2426, \"to\": 2604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The prolonged migration process inEuropean countriesfurther exacerbates the risk of displaced communities experiencing mental health symptoms and disorders.\", \"from\": 2605, \"to\": 2761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Research further showsthat factors like unstable living conditions, and the breakdown of social and cultural ties further compound vulnerability, increasing the risk of mental health symptoms and disorders amongdisplaced communities.\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Forcing people to leave the only places they can find shelter to accommodate events like the Olympic Games only compounds the trauma many have already experienced.\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The French government's stance on French Muslim women athleteswearing hijabsremains one of the most contentious issues surrounding the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 3163, \"to\": 3313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3167, \"end\": 3173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9858621550426128, \"rank\": 0.012459676851875533, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3197, \"end\": 3203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9858621550426128, \"rank\": 0.012459676851875533, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3204, \"end\": 3210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.7910385495601301, \"rank\": 0.26416087822154305, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In September 2023, French Sports MinisterAmelie Oudea-Casterareiterated that French athletes will be banned from wearing hijab.\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3392, \"end\": 3398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9858621550426128, \"rank\": 0.012459676851875533, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That casts doubt on how inclusive the Paris Games will be.\", \"from\": 3443, \"to\": 3501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The French government's ideological view regarding religious symbols directly conflicts with the IOC's regulations that permit athletes to express their religious beliefs, including wearing religious attirelike the hijab.\", \"from\": 3503, \"to\": 3724, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3507, \"end\": 3513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9858621550426128, \"rank\": 0.012459676851875533, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3600, \"end\": 3603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.018121785233279e-25, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheUnited Nations Human Rights OfficeandAmnesty Internationalhave said such bans infringe on Muslim women's rights and freedom.\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3819, \"end\": 3825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.7910385495601301, \"rank\": 0.26416087822154305, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Furthermore, various Muslim women athletes likeDiaba Konat\\u00e9have left France, or are thinking of leaving the country, in search of sporting environments that respect their religious beliefs.\", \"from\": 3855, \"to\": 4044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3876, \"end\": 3882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.7910385495601301, \"rank\": 0.26416087822154305, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}, {\"begin\": 3924, \"end\": 3930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.8484963255544216, \"rank\": 0.1157073647126074, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hijab ban not only violates thefundamental right of Muslim womento follow their religious beliefs, but also contradicts thecore principles of equalityespoused by the Olympics.\", \"from\": 4046, \"to\": 4225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4102, \"end\": 4108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.7910385495601301, \"rank\": 0.26416087822154305, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hijab ban also starkly contradicts the French government's proclaimed commitment to equality through sports by effectivelyexcluding Muslim womenwho want to wear a hijab.\", \"from\": 4227, \"to\": 4400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4270, \"end\": 4276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9858621550426128, \"rank\": 0.012459676851875533, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4363, \"end\": 4369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.7910385495601301, \"rank\": 0.26416087822154305, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despiteclear and documentedinstances of human rights abuses linked to the upcoming Paris Olympics, much of the western media and political leaders have remained conspicuously silent.\", \"from\": 4402, \"to\": 4584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4485, \"end\": 4499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many western athletes, commentators, news outlets and politicians were previously critical of the human rights records of countries like Azerbaijan, Russia, China and Qatar when they hosted mega sporting events.\", \"from\": 4586, \"to\": 4797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4723, \"end\": 4733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azerbaijan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999631655, \"rank\": 3.600690995999662e-11, \"text\": \"Azerbaijan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azerbaijan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azerbaijan\"}, {\"begin\": 4735, \"end\": 4741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.999980632308707, \"rank\": 1.8389433404056343e-05, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 4743, \"end\": 4748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.99929582720832, \"rank\": 0.0007023732765106739, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 4753, \"end\": 4758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.0055484260123259e-12, \"text\": \"Qatar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many claimed that those governments were using sporting events tolaunder their human rights records.\", \"from\": 4798, \"to\": 4898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some evencalled for boycottsand bans.\", \"from\": 4900, \"to\": 4937, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet, that kind of criticism is rarely directed inward as well.\", \"from\": 4939, \"to\": 5001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Researchershave previously argued that western media reports human rights abuses in the West with a tilted bias suggesting westerners are morally superior and concerned,framing issuesas isolated rather than systemic.\", \"from\": 5003, \"to\": 5219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance,a recent studyoutlines how British media portrayed English cricketer Azeem Rafiq's allegations of racism against the Yorkshire County Cricket Club.\", \"from\": 5221, \"to\": 5381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5261, \"end\": 5268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9780221699857519, \"rank\": 0.02200385627878925, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 5285, \"end\": 5292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\", \"score\": 0.9530643050218779, \"rank\": 0.049246468043395115, \"text\": \"English\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\"}, {\"begin\": 5303, \"end\": 5314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azeem_Rafiq\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Azeem Rafiq\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azeem_Rafiq\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azeem_Rafiq\"}, {\"begin\": 5351, \"end\": 5380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorkshire_County_Cricket_Club\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yorkshire County Cricket Club\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorkshire_County_Cricket_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorkshire_County_Cricket_Club\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The media narrative suggested that British society is aware of racism, accepts criticism and is ready to act.\", \"from\": 5382, \"to\": 5491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5417, \"end\": 5432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_society\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British society\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_society\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_society\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the same media also portrayed Rafiq as anoutsider and his allegations as isolated incidents.\", \"from\": 5493, \"to\": 5594, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Western media's inconsistent condemnation ofsportswashingand limited criticism of hosts in the West obfuscates a harsh reality.\", \"from\": 5596, \"to\": 5723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These mega events, whether in Beijing or Los Angeles, Rio de Janeiro or Paris, come at a grim human cost.\", \"from\": 5724, \"to\": 5829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5754, \"end\": 5761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"score\": 0.9999999999959073, \"rank\": 4.010585392485706e-12, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\"}, {\"begin\": 5765, \"end\": 5776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999960896275, \"rank\": 2.8475691970481965e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 5778, \"end\": 5792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9999999998617568, \"rank\": 1.3816341792381122e-10, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 5796, \"end\": 5801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999690948421616, \"rank\": 3.090611319287601e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's high time the West looked in the mirror.\", \"from\": 5831, \"to\": 5876, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 Olympics will not be the scene of renewed efforts toward \\\"social responsibility and respect for internationally recognized human rights.\\\"\", \"from\": 5877, \"to\": 6029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5887, \"end\": 5900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In many ways, it's already a failure in those respects.\", \"from\": 6030, \"to\": 6085, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After more than 100 years of repeated harms, perhaps it's time to consign Olympism to the dustbin of history.\", \"from\": 6087, \"to\": 6196, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We must speak bluntly and honestly about these mega sporting events, identify their limitations and voice meaningful opposition regardless of which nation is hosting.\", \"from\": 6197, \"to\": 6363, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If that means a world without the Olympics, so be it.\", \"from\": 6364, \"to\": 6417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2026,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 6419, \"to\": 6473, \"entities\": []}]}"